-- Indian banks borrowed 17.7 bln rupees via MSF on Jan 15 - RBI
-- By Neha Dasgupta
-- Thu Jan 16, 2014 12:05AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Jan 16 (Reuters) - Indian banks borrowed 17.7 billion rupees ($287.55 million) from the central bank's marginal standing facility (MSF) window on Jan. 15 for one day, sharply lower than the 139.77 billion rupees borrowed on Jan. 13 for two days.

The Reserve Bank of India cut the MSF rate by 25 basis points (bps) to 8.75 percent on Oct. 29. It had raised the rate by 200 bps to 10.25 percent in mid-July.